tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Starting Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Everfrost&Comment=1">Everfrost</a></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Secondary Zones:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Eruds Crossing&Comment=1">Eruds Crossing</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Lake Rathetear&Comment=1">Lake Rathetear</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Dagnors Cauldron&Comment=1">Dagnors Cauldron</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Guk, Lower&Comment=1">Guk, Lower</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Oasis of Marr&Comment=1">Oasis of Marr</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Highpass Hold&Comment=1">Highpass Hold</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Qeynos Aqueduct&Comment=1">Qeynos Aqueduct</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Neriak, Commons&Comment=1">Neriak, Commons</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Unrest&Comment=1">Unrest</a></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Items Needed:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Description:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">This is actually the quest for the runes needed to create the 49th wizard spell Ice Comet.  However, if you are a Wizard and not quite 49th level yet, then simply keep the Staff of the Wheel, and the Star of Eyes.
<br><br>
<b>1. </b>The quest begins in Everfrost.  Go to approx. loc 3000, -2000, and speak to the wizard Sulgar.  He will give you a chest which is no rent, and a book, which isn’t.  
<br><br>
<b>2. </b>Sulgar tells of a great wheel, which was smashed, and each of the 10 spokes scattered across the Norath.  The book gives a small poem giving a clue to the location of each spoke.  Here are the locations of each spoke/rod (each is no drop):
<br><br>
<b>Azia</b> – It is on the bottom of the ocean by Erud’s Crossing, just past the half-sunken boat. Loc –1100, 2300.
<br><br>
<b>Beza</b> – This one is actually in Everfrost, in the underground caves by the river.  Enter the caves through the northernmost hole in the ice, and follow the wall to the right until you come to a room with a stone ‘hut’.  The rod is in the hut, guarded by 3 Ice Boned Skeletons.
<br><br>
<b>Caza</b> – This rod is in lake Rathe, beneath the island with the Aviak guarded pedestal.  On the opposite side of the pedestal, there is an underwater entrance.  Follow it all the way down to a large, underwater cavern.  In the center is a tower.  The rod is in the middle of the floor at the top of the tower.  It is guarded by aquatic goblins.
<br><br>
<b>Dena</b> – This rod is just outside the entrance to Kedge keep in Dagnor’s Cauldron.  The entrance is underwater, off of the island in the middle of the cauldron.  The rod is to the right of the ancient gateway.
<br><br>
<b>Ena</b> – Unless you are actually high enough level to cast Ice comet, you will most likely need help retrieving this rod.  It is in the re-animated hand room in Lower Guk.  The ceiling of the re-animated hand room is water.  Jump up and swim to the small alcove located above.  The rod is lying on the floor there.
<br><br>
</b>Fana</b> – In the Oasis of Marr, there is an underwater tower on the east side of the island.  The rod is on the floor at the top of the tower.  It is guarded by aquatic goblins.
<br><br>
</b>Geza</b> – Beneath the waterfall closest to the Tiger Inn in Highhold, lies the rod.
<br><br>
</b>Heda</b> – Beneath Qeynos in the aqueducts, in the shark pit.
<br><br>
</b>Izah</b> – In Neriak (commons), there is a bar called the Blind Fish.  There are 4 windows that look underwater.  The rod spawns just on the other side of the windows, and can actually be grabbed through the window.
<br><br>
</b>Jaka</b> – Finally, this rod is in Unrest.  To the right of the house, there is a small moat.  Within the moat, there is a small tunnel, and a smaller entrance to the right of that.  Take the small entrance, and it leads to a room where the rod is located.
<br><br>
<b>3. </b>Take the rods and place them within the chest given by Sulgar, and hit combine.  When I completed this quest, the rods combined successfully for me on my first try, but I have heard that it is not a 100% success rate.
<br><br>
<b>4. </b>If you give these items to Sulgar, he will give you the runes needed to create the Ice Comet spell.  The runes are, however, no drop.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Manawyddan (Lanys Tvyl)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Quest Reward:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>Staff of the Wheel / Star of Eyes</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma"></font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>1HB INT+10 HP+10 MANA+10  Effect: Identify</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>7.2</b> (average of <b>5</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this quest:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratequest.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Quest</OPTION><OPTI